`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"As I said earlier, perfect software is a myth. Despite being a myth, there is something that we call a Minimum Viable Product ( MVP ). Every product that you are building, will have minimum viability to be accepted as a functional product."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"MVP can be best described as a mid-point between the earlier stages of the development process and the final product, meeting all the fundamental requirements of the product."}),`
